div.div: Created new branch saforem2/format-sidebery-settings in saforem2/textfox

Changes So I made some decisions that (I think, hopefully) are logical and simplify things a bit but feel free to weigh in:
Allow passing the profile directory as an argument directly to tf-install.sh , e.g.: bash tf-install.sh Example: #[2025-06-07 @ 19:33:31][~/p/s/textfox][ saforem2/fix-install][] [ 3s] ; bash tf-install.sh "~/Library/Application Support/Firefox/Profiles/3nvn2a07.default-release" (14 more lines were trimmed) If no arguments received, prompt user for input: Example: #[2025-06-07 @ 19:33:16][~/p/s/textfox][ saforem2/fix-install][] ; bash tf-install.sh (16 more lines were trimmed) Test Cases Handle Different Cases #[2025-06-07 @ 19:32:10][~/p/s/textfox][ saforem2/fix-install][] ; test_cases=("~/Library//Application Support/Firefox/Profiles/3nvn2a07.default-release" "'~/Library//Application Support/Firefox/Profiles/3nvn2a07.default-release'" "\"~/Library//Application Support/Firefox/Profiles/3nvn2a07.default-release\"" "~/Library//Application Support/Firefox/Profiles//3nvn2a07.default-release/" "~/broken_path" ) ; printf "%s\n" "${test_cases[@]}" (91 more lines were trimmed) Copilot Summary This pull request refactors the tf-install.sh script to improve its structure, readability, and functionality. The changes include modularizing the code into functions, adding input validation and path sanitization, and improving the user experience with better feedback and error handling. Code Refactoring and Modularity: Replaced the inline script logic with modular functions ( print_logo , clean_path , backup_existing_profile , copy_chrome , install_user_js , tf_install ) to improve readability and maintainability. Input Validation and Path Handling: Added the clean_path function to sanitize and normalize user-provided paths (e.g., expanding ~ , removing trailing slashes, and handling quotes). This ensures robust handling of input paths. Enhanced User Experience: Introduced a print_logo function to display a logo at the start of the script, improving the visual appeal of the installation process. Improved error handling and feedback by validating the existence of the Firefox profile directory and providing clear messages when paths are invalid or operations are skipped. Backup and Safety: Added the backup_existing_profile function to automatically back up the existing chrome directory with a timestamped name, replacing the previous manual backup prompt.
